19:59.929 --> 20:00.850
You know, I love what

20:01.346 --> 20:09.958
What Proverbs 24 verse 6 says, strategic planning is the key to warfare to when you need a lot of good counsel.

20:11.700 --> 20:16.546
You know, one of the ways to receive good counsel here at potential churches through our connect groups.

20:17.768 --> 20:25.138
And you know, we don't host connect groups throughout the week because we need one more thing to do or you need one more thing to add to your calendar.

20:25.506 --> 20:36.442
No, we host connect groups because we truly believe that the destiny that God has in store for you is so vast that you can't possibly accomplish it on your own.

20:37.083 --> 20:38.125
See, we need each other.

20:39.887 --> 20:44.434
Church isn't about coming into a building, it's about being integrated into a community.

20:45.122 --> 20:57.297
Something happens when we get into community, when we meet in houses throughout the week to comfort one another, to encourage one another, to challenge and hold one another accountable, to pray for one another.

20:57.397 --> 21:01.022
It changes the atmosphere in our lives.

21:02.484 --> 21:07.410
You know, Proverbs also reminds us that as iron sharpens iron, so does one man sharpen another.

21:08.962 --> 21:16.459
And we each have to ask ourselves the question, the people that you are surrounding yourself with, do they sharpen your passion for God?

21:16.479 --> 21:19.045
Or do they dull your passion for Him?

21:20.989 --> 21:22.553
Listen, I want to encourage you.

21:23.134 --> 21:24.818
Listen, don't do life alone.

21:25.570 --> 21:32.039
If you're not already involved in the connect group, we're launching our new season of connect groups come September.

21:32.059 --> 21:45.396
And listen, I encourage you, listen, get signed up, get involved in the connect group, get around people that are in a similar season of life that can come around you, that can rally around you, that can speak life over you when you're going through a difficult challenge.

21:46.217 --> 21:52.626
That can be there to cry for you, to cry with you, to pray not just for you, but to also pray with you.

21:53.666 --> 21:55.989
That can declare the promises of God over your life.

21:58.152 --> 22:05.241
It is a huge part of our success and growing in our walk with God is who we choose to align ourselves with.

22:05.281 --> 22:11.269
And you know another practical step in our personal growth and in our walk with God is the step of baptism.

22:12.631 --> 22:21.362
You know we've got beach baptism coming up tomorrow from two to five p.m. And you know baptism is the very first thing that God asks us

22:21.506 --> 22:24.250
to do once we've accepted Christ as our Lord and Savior.

22:25.291 --> 22:28.536
And you know what it says in Romans chapter six, verse four.

22:29.517 --> 22:32.441
For we died and were buried with Christ by baptism.

22:33.162 --> 22:39.331
And just as Christ was raised from the dead by the glorious power of the Father, now we also may live new lives.

22:39.751 --> 22:47.422
Galatians 3.27 says it like this, for all who were baptized into Christ have clothed yourselves with Christ.

22:48.383 --> 22:50.386
See, that's what baptism represents.

22:51.202 --> 22:54.706
It's the new life that we have in Christ.

22:55.627 --> 23:01.495
You know, we say here often at potential church that to get baptized is to put on your God jersey.

23:01.815 --> 23:03.898
Why do we say that?

23:04.058 --> 23:07.141
Why do we use that terminology, putting on the God jersey?

23:08.083 --> 23:10.566
Because see, that's the picture that it paints.

23:11.707 --> 23:17.394
When we go under that water and come back up, it is a representation of putting on

23:17.570 --> 23:27.223
a God Jersey, letting the world know that we are on God's team, that he's done something in our lives, that he's done something in our hearts, that we are no longer the same.

23:27.243 --> 23:35.474
See, when we go underneath that water, it paints that picture of the old us being buried with Christ.

23:35.534 --> 23:41.522
And when we're brought up out of that water, the new us being raised to life with Christ.

23:42.274 --> 23:43.276
It paints a picture.

23:43.296 --> 23:44.337
It tells a story.

23:44.397 --> 23:48.664
It's an outward expression of an internal transformation.

23:50.166 --> 23:55.554
And you know, sometimes I think maybe baptism is a little bit intimidating because we don't fully understand it.

23:55.574 --> 24:02.985
We think that, well, if we get baptized, if we make this public declaration, then all of a sudden we're held accountable to that.

24:03.025 --> 24:06.290
And we can't make the same mistakes that we used to make.

24:06.722 --> 24:15.932
I mean, what if we get baptized and our family is there to witness it and they're excited about, then all of a sudden the next day we lose our temper and we yell at our spouse and say hurtful things.

24:18.935 --> 24:21.959
But you see, baptism doesn't mean that we're perfect.

24:22.279 --> 24:27.785
It just means that we are making a public declaration that we serve a perfect God.

24:27.805 --> 24:32.530
And listen, that's the message that the world needs to see and they need to see it from you and I.

24:33.922 --> 24:36.025
You know, baptism is not for anyone else.

24:36.086 --> 24:37.087
Baptism is for you.

24:39.050 --> 24:44.720
And, you know, I understand and I recognize that many of us in here come from different religious backgrounds.

24:44.800 --> 24:48.626
And, you know, in South Florida, I know many of us come from a Catholic background.

24:49.608 --> 24:52.472
And you say, well, why was baptized as an infant?

24:53.534 --> 24:58.302
If I get baptized as an adult, I don't know how my family's gonna respond to that.

24:58.322 --> 25:00.946
I don't know what my parents are gonna think about that.

25:01.250 --> 25:07.519
And you see, when we get baptized as an adult, we're not disgracing what our parents did.

25:07.559 --> 25:10.703
We're fulfilling the promise that our parents made.

25:12.246 --> 25:15.831
They committed to raise you in a godly household.

25:16.291 --> 25:19.977
They consecrated you to Christ.

25:20.057 --> 25:29.490
And when we get baptized after making the decision for ourselves that Jesus Christ is Lord, came to earth, died on that cross and that He rose from the grave.

25:29.890 --> 25:33.153
And we step into that water and make that declaration.

25:33.513 --> 25:35.655
It is fulfilling that promise.

25:37.677 --> 25:42.862
And you know, to not be baptized after accepting Christ is actually disobedience.

25:45.605 --> 25:50.810
And if you're waiting on anybody else's blessing to be baptized, listen, you have God's blessing.

25:51.810 --> 25:53.332
That's all the blessing that you need.

25:53.392 --> 25:59.858
Not choosing to be baptized actually separates us from God.

26:00.770 --> 26:04.696
It puts up a wall between God's blessing and us.

26:05.377 --> 26:10.185
And listen, I want to encourage you today, if you have made that decision, but you have yet to follow Christ in baptism.

26:10.686 --> 26:12.709
Listen, I want to encourage you.

26:13.330 --> 26:14.652
Make that decision.

26:15.093 --> 26:17.417
Join us at Beach baptism tomorrow.

26:17.978 --> 26:20.562
Listen, I believe that God's going to pour out a blessing over your life.

26:21.058 --> 26:23.200
You say, well, I'm worried about what my family's going to say.

26:23.240 --> 26:24.161
Listen, trust God.

26:24.582 --> 26:26.944
Trust God with your family's reaction.

26:27.024 --> 26:29.267
Trust God with your family's hearts.

26:29.307 --> 26:32.290
God can do in one moment what we can't do in a lifetime.

26:32.530 --> 26:46.885
And that may be the one single decision that you need to make this weekend to walk out your destiny, to go beyond the sandbox and to step into the purpose that God has for you.

26:46.905 --> 26:47.506
And you know,

26:47.682 --> 26:52.147
We actually have a story of baptism that we want to share with you.

26:52.167 --> 26:55.010
And so Carson, why don't you introduce our guest?

26:55.291 --> 26:57.854
Yes, we have a very special student coming out.

26:57.914 --> 27:03.620
Her name is Nev. Let's give it up for Nev. She's going to join us.

27:03.760 --> 27:04.862
Yes, yes, yes.

27:04.982 --> 27:06.984
Now, Nev has an incredible story.

27:07.445 --> 27:10.568
She actually started attending the church quite a while ago.

27:10.608 --> 27:13.752
She is a veteran now here at Potential Church.

27:14.032 --> 27:15.794
But she started attending quite a while ago.

27:15.906 --> 27:21.914
And over time, she felt that nudge to get baptized, take that next step in her faith.

27:22.255 --> 27:26.340
And so she did that, she got baptized at a beach baptism, which is awesome.

27:26.620 --> 27:33.810
She took that step, fast forward a little further down the road, and she ended up attending our uproar camp, our uproar conference camp.

27:34.351 --> 27:39.698
And she did some crazy things in order to get the money to go.

27:39.970 --> 27:42.352
But you know, that has had a huge impact on her life.

27:42.593 --> 27:44.975
And it's been incredible to see how far she's come.

27:45.015 --> 27:50.160
You know, she is serving in many different areas here at potential church and in potential youth.

27:50.560 --> 27:54.844
And she is a part of our right squad, which is our leadership, core leadership student group.

27:54.864 --> 27:56.286
So she's come a really long way.

27:56.686 --> 28:02.572
Nev, now, you know, talking about baptism, what really got you, you know, what made you want to do that?

28:02.632 --> 28:05.975
What got you to feel that need of this is something I need to do.

28:06.556 --> 28:09.138
Well, I had only been coming to,

28:09.378 --> 28:33.106
Potential church for two weeks until I got baptized so I saw how amazing Everyone was so happy all the time was like what is this like whatever they're on I want that give me that please and so I wish I just spoke to myself quietly to myself and really took some time to think whatever it takes to get to that place I am completely willing to do because I

28:33.698 --> 28:42.489
I really wouldn't be the person I am today if I didn't take that leap of faith because I was watching you and Jess and Gabe when you guys were still in high school.

28:42.509 --> 28:43.670
So I was like, I that.

28:44.011 --> 28:49.317
And so the fact that you are now my leader and I'm standing right next to you talking about that is a really big deal.

28:49.377 --> 28:51.340
Baptism is a very big deal in my book.

28:51.941 --> 28:52.321
Awesome.

28:52.441 --> 28:52.722
Awesome.

28:52.742 --> 28:53.643
That's so cool to hear.

28:53.703 --> 28:54.023
Yes.

28:54.143 --> 28:54.424
Yes.

28:57.247 --> 29:02.674
Now you had talked about, you had said, mentioned in there, I don't know if you did on purpose, but you had mentioned whatever it takes.

29:02.818 --> 29:11.091
And that is the tagline for this year's camp to really instill in the students a sense of, we will do whatever it takes to change this world for the better.

29:11.611 --> 29:17.400
Now with that, you did, from what I've heard, you did some crazy things to get the money to go to camp.

29:17.420 --> 29:18.442
What were some of those things?

29:18.902 --> 29:21.466
Well, this is weird.

29:21.506 --> 29:22.448
This is really weird.

29:22.568 --> 29:24.250
I had to get a sponsorship.

29:24.691 --> 29:27.696
So my father and I sat down and we were like, what can I do?

29:27.816 --> 29:29.298
And my father said,

29:29.474 --> 29:33.499
I'm going to do 1,000 push-ups in 10 days and find people to give me money.

29:34.119 --> 29:38.184
I don't remember what I said, but it was somewhere along the lines of, I'm sorry, what?

29:38.625 --> 29:39.586
Please tell me again.

29:39.606 --> 29:48.677
And so I had to do 1,000 push-ups in 10 days, so I did 10 push-ups every hour for 10 hours a day for 10 days.

29:48.717 --> 29:56.626
And I ended up raising over $400 for myself to go, and I gave the church extra money for someone else to go.

29:57.986 --> 29:59.968
Yes, that is incredible.

30:00.169 --> 30:04.694
That is absolutely amazing, you know, that you would put in that work because you really wanted to go.

30:04.734 --> 30:07.938
That shows that it meant something to you.

30:08.159 --> 30:14.387
Now with camp, if there's a parent in here who's maybe on the fence of, should I send my kid?

30:14.427 --> 30:15.228
Should I not?

30:15.248 --> 30:18.031
Or maybe there's a student in here who's on the fence of, should I go?

30:18.111 --> 30:18.572
Should I not?

30:19.313 --> 30:23.538
From your mouth, why is it so important to go to camp?

30:23.618 --> 30:27.765
I can't really change my life, because at that point, I didn't know what I wanted.

30:27.785 --> 30:30.370
I had a relationship with God.

30:30.390 --> 30:31.151
I was baptized.

30:31.211 --> 30:38.243
But I still was very unclear of what I was supposed to do with this relationship that I have with God.

30:38.764 --> 30:41.509
And going to camp, it completely changed my life around.

30:41.649 --> 30:44.774
I realized things that I could have never thought on my own.

30:44.874 --> 30:49.362
I had an amazing opportunity to watch these speakers right in front of me.

30:49.474 --> 30:51.737
telling me all these things, just feeding me.

30:51.757 --> 30:53.779
And it was absolutely life changing.

30:53.899 --> 30:58.444
At the end of that conference, I was speaking to my best friends, Dakota and Patrick.

30:58.865 --> 31:02.469
And we were taught, because they were in riot squad, because they're older than me.

31:02.549 --> 31:07.554
And I was like, you know, but by the time I'm ninth grade, I am going to be in riot squad.

31:07.915 --> 31:14.202
And in January of this year, you and Jess took me to the green room and invited me to be a part of riot squad.

31:14.242 --> 31:18.066
So without a war camp, I wouldn't have known I wanted that.

31:18.210 --> 31:24.496
And I wouldn't be again next to you talking about this so that the camp was a very big deal.

31:24.556 --> 31:25.737
Camp is a very big deal.

31:25.757 --> 31:26.678
Awesome, awesome.

31:26.698 --> 31:27.519
Thank you so much.

31:27.899 --> 31:28.780
Can we give it up for me?

31:32.003 --> 31:32.744
Yes, yes.

31:32.884 --> 31:38.810
She is one of the many incredible students that attend our potential youth.

31:38.930 --> 31:41.432
And you guys heard it from her, straight from her mouth.

31:42.153 --> 31:43.274
Camp changed her life.

31:43.935 --> 31:47.378
It was a huge part of the change that happened in her.

31:47.458 --> 31:48.900
Her family has noticed it.

31:49.622 --> 31:51.004
Her friends have noticed it.

31:51.785 --> 31:55.992
Her life is completely altered because she went to camp.

31:56.754 --> 31:57.735
That's why we do this.

31:57.795 --> 32:00.199
We don't do camp to just have a good time.

32:00.560 --> 32:03.445
We do have an incredible time, but that's not why we do it.

32:03.986 --> 32:10.717
We do it because we truly believe deep within our hearts that if a student goes to camp, their life will be forever changed.

32:11.298 --> 32:13.682
They will never be the same.

32:14.338 --> 32:26.935
And I challenge you today, if maybe you don't have a young person who's in middle school or high school, or maybe you don't have that age group, maybe sponsor a kid.

32:27.616 --> 32:30.019
Maybe sponsor a kid who wants to go really bad.

32:30.800 --> 32:33.484
They really want to go to camp, but they don't have the money to do it.

32:34.505 --> 32:35.767
Be a part of that solution.

32:36.508 --> 32:38.330
I promise you, God will honor you for that.

32:38.731 --> 32:44.178
For being a part of life change within a student that will radically, completely change their lives.

32:44.258 --> 32:46.281
And through that, your life will change as well.

32:46.641 --> 32:48.003
Please don't miss this opportunity.

32:48.725 --> 32:50.587
This is huge, huge.

32:51.328 --> 32:53.491
Our goal at Potential Youth is to change the world.

32:54.132 --> 32:56.215
To not just be a part of something that happens.

32:56.936 --> 32:58.619
Every week, you know, we go in there and we meet.

32:58.679 --> 32:59.841
It's not the goal.

33:00.382 --> 33:02.425
The goal is to change the world.

33:03.326 --> 33:07.272
And that happens through different events such as camp.

33:07.292 --> 33:08.874
So please don't miss out on that opportunity.

33:09.234 --> 33:11.698
Please take advantage of that.

33:11.810 --> 33:15.816
As Tyler talked about earlier, the first thing we have to do is outwit the enemy.

33:16.336 --> 33:20.062
And we do that through good alliances, strategy, all those different things.

33:20.863 --> 33:23.827
The next thing we have to do is outplay our opponents.

33:24.528 --> 33:25.389
I love this one.

33:25.690 --> 33:26.210
I really do.

33:26.250 --> 33:29.195
It's kind of the underdog story almost.

33:29.495 --> 33:33.080
The idea that it's not about being bigger, it's about being better.

33:33.961 --> 33:40.210
And for me, I love Survivor, and there's a lot of underdog opportunities in Survivor.

33:40.642 --> 33:43.825
And one comes to my mind of a guy named Aussie.

33:43.845 --> 33:48.950
He's a scrawny guy, doesn't look fast, strong, athletic.

33:48.970 --> 33:50.211
He doesn't look any of those things.

33:51.172 --> 33:57.918
And so it shocked everyone when out of, there's usually about 19 competitions throughout a season of Survivor, he won 18.

33:58.579 --> 34:01.242
He lost one competition throughout the entirety of it.

34:02.082 --> 34:10.130
And as they investigated his background and his story, they found that his life was really designed to win Survivor.

34:10.978 --> 34:18.565
the way he grew up, what he did, all of that stuff really set his life up to be good at survivor.

34:19.226 --> 34:20.868
And kind of it's the same thing in our life.

34:20.988 --> 34:23.750
It's the idea that train what you want to be good at.

34:25.112 --> 34:27.214
Train in the area you want to succeed in.

34:27.894 --> 34:33.660
You know, I know sometimes it's, you know, I'll hear people say things like, you know, I wish my relationship was closer to God.

34:34.861 --> 34:37.664
But you're hanging out with people who are pushing you further away from it.

34:38.925 --> 34:39.826
That doesn't work.

34:40.194 --> 34:43.620
It's like training in football to beat Stephen Curry in basketball.

34:44.000 --> 34:44.781
That doesn't work.

34:45.643 --> 34:48.087
Train in where the area that you want to be good at.

34:48.848 --> 34:54.938
There's the best underdog story in the history of time, as far as I'm concerned, can be found in 1 Samuel 17.

34:56.040 --> 35:07.378
It says, David replied to the Philistine, you come to me with sword, spear, and javelin, but I come to you in the name of the Lord of Heaven's armies, the God of the armies of Israel, whom you have defied.

35:07.778 --> 35:11.241
Today the Lord will conquer you, and I will kill you and cut off your head.

35:11.542 --> 35:15.365
And then I will give you the dead bodies of your men to the birds and the wild animals.

35:15.826 --> 35:18.868
And the whole world will know that there is a God in Israel.

35:19.229 --> 35:24.314
And everyone assembled here will know that the Lord rescues his people, but not with sword and spear.

35:24.574 --> 35:26.956
This is the Lord's battle, and he will give you to us.

35:27.737 --> 35:30.339
For those of you who don't know, this is the story of David and Goliath.

35:31.040 --> 35:32.762
David took down a giant.

35:32.782 --> 35:37.426
David, a small kid, he was a kid at this point, took down a giant.

35:38.306 --> 35:41.149
And oftentimes, we think of that as David's work.

35:41.789 --> 35:45.633
David's hard work was taking down Goliath.

35:45.653 --> 35:47.395
In reality, that wasn't his hard work.

35:47.435 --> 35:48.336
That was God's hard work.

35:48.896 --> 35:49.497
God did that.

35:49.577 --> 35:50.398
David can't do that.

35:51.339 --> 35:56.444
What David's hard work was deciding that he was going to take on Goliath.

35:57.445 --> 36:01.028
Be courageous enough to step to him and say, I can do this with God.

36:01.829 --> 36:06.994
The only way that this happens is if God shows up.

36:07.106 --> 36:16.140
There's honor from God in those situations where we step to a situation where we tell God, God, if you don't intervene here, this isn't gonna work.

36:16.160 --> 36:18.844
I'm gonna go fall flat on my face, I'm gonna fail.

36:20.246 --> 36:29.601
When we set ourself up in situations where we can only succeed with God's intervention, miraculous things happen.

36:30.462 --> 36:33.327
Worlds get changed, lives are changed.

36:34.528 --> 36:35.570
And all of a sudden,

36:35.970 --> 36:38.493
This isn't just a place in Cooper City.

36:39.474 --> 36:42.877
All of a sudden, potential church is a part of something that's changing the world.

36:43.578 --> 36:44.779
That's something I wanna be a part of.

36:45.680 --> 36:54.088
I would hate to get to heaven and find out that I missed out on that blessing because I was too unwilling to do the hard work.

36:54.689 --> 37:01.256
I was too unwilling to step into fearful situations and to just ask God, God, I need you to intervene in this.

37:01.476 --> 37:03.538
I can't do it without you.

37:03.874 --> 37:09.720
And I think there's true, with that humility, God really honors that lifestyle.

37:09.740 --> 37:11.762
And lives are changed, the world is changed.

37:12.143 --> 37:14.105
And that's something that I wanna be a part of.

37:14.125 --> 37:15.607
That's right, that's so good.

37:15.687 --> 37:33.746
And kind of as we've been saying, if we're gonna grow, we've gotta have a strategy, we've gotta outwit the enemy, we've gotta outplay our opponents, it's not about getting bigger, it's about getting better, it's not about moving into the next season, it's about conquering the season.

37:33.954 --> 37:35.316
that God has us in right now.

37:35.356 --> 37:48.033
And where I want to land us today is when we do those things, when we are walking closely with God, it gives us what we need to outlast our circumstances.

37:49.735 --> 37:51.578
You know, Jesus Christ came to earth.

37:51.638 --> 37:57.265
He died a shameful death so that we could spend an eternity in heaven with Him.

37:58.447 --> 38:03.794
But you know, I believe that Christ also came so that we could live a victorious life

38:04.002 --> 38:04.543
here on earth.

38:06.046 --> 38:26.802
And you know, one of the things that I've learned in my own fight for faith, and how many of you know sometimes faith is a fight, sometimes it requires a fight to hold on to your faith when your situation says it's impossible, when the doctors give you a bad report, when it seems like all hope is lost, we have to hold on to our faith.

38:27.330 --> 38:34.217
And one of the things that I've learned is the battle is not one to those who fight the hardest necessarily, but those who fight the longest.

38:35.799 --> 38:41.165
Those who don't quit, those who don't give up, those who stand the test of time.

38:43.848 --> 38:44.148
You know what?

38:44.368 --> 38:51.436
It tells us in James chapter 1 verse 12 that blessed is the one who perseveres under trial.

38:52.477 --> 38:56.882
The one who stands the test for he will receive the crown.

38:57.186 --> 39:03.975
that God has promised to those who love Him, that they will receive the crown of life.

39:05.437 --> 39:06.318
And you may say, you know what?

39:06.359 --> 39:08.762
That's great, Tyler, but that's not my story.

39:11.125 --> 39:13.008
God, He has left me.

39:13.068 --> 39:14.409
He's abandoned me.

39:14.470 --> 39:19.657
There's no way that a loving God could allow this to enter my life.

39:19.697 --> 39:23.602
And I just want to share with you, first Peter chapter four, I believe you're going to be encouraged today.

39:23.778 --> 39:35.500
Verse 12, the message puts it like this, friends, when life gets really difficult, don't jump to the conclusion that God isn't on the job.

39:36.241 --> 39:37.403
Instead, be glad.

39:37.504 --> 39:39.507
Some translations say rejoice.

39:40.469 --> 39:41.030
Rejoice.

